npcText: You notice her pale complexion, and she seems to be quite tired. She is holding a small hankerchief, occasionally dabbing at her forehead.

playerText: How are you feeling today, Miss?
npcText: Maisie: I've been better, to be honest.

playerText: Oh dear. Can I help in any way?
Will you be alright for the duration of the trip?
npcText: Maisie: *smiles* Well, I don't think my condition can get any worse. *cough* *cough*
Maisie: I'm not too sure, honestly. *cough* My vision is a little cloudy... I can't really read my ticket... *cough*
